  <h2>Best practices</h2>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>Order = Matching</strong>: The 1st Tab matches the 1st TabPanel, the 2nd to the 2nd, etc.</li>
    <li><strong>Unique group name</strong>: All Tabs in a group must have the same <code class="inline-code">name</code></li>
    <li><strong>Default checked</strong>: Always set one tab with <code class="inline-code">checked</code> to avoid empty display</li>
    <li><strong>Slot structure</strong>: Use <code class="inline-code">slot="tabs"</code> for tabs and <code class="inline-code">slot="panels"</code> for content</li>
    <li><strong>Logical order</strong>: Organize tabs left to right by importance</li>
    <li><strong>Number of tabs</strong>: Limit to 5-7 tabs to avoid cognitive overload</li>
    <li><strong>Clear labels</strong>: Use short, descriptive labels</li>
    <li><strong>Relevant icons</strong>: Add icons to improve visual recognition</li>
    <li><strong>Consistent variant</strong>: Use the same variant as the rest of the interface</li>
    <li><strong>Distinct content</strong>: Each panel should have sufficiently distinct content</li>
    <li><strong>ZERO JavaScript</strong>: The system works entirely in pure CSS</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>CSS-only architecture</h2>
  <p>The Tabs system uses the <strong>radio button technique</strong> for 100% CSS operation:</p>
  <ul>
    <li><code class="inline-code">&lt;input type=\"radio\"&gt;</code> are hidden with <code class="inline-code">opacity: 0</code></li>
    <li><code class="inline-code">&lt;label&gt;</code> elements act as styled clickable buttons</li>
    <li>The <code class="inline-code">:checked</code> pseudo-class detects the active tab</li>
    <li>The sibling selector <code class="inline-code">~</code> shows the corresponding panel</li>
    <li>CSS pattern: <code class="inline-code">#id:checked ~ .tabs-panels > [data-tab=\"id\"]</code></li>
  </ul>

